# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Aeris — Environment Variables
# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in whatever you want to use.
# Everything below is optional; the app runs with no secrets at all.
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# --- Analytics (optional) ---------------------------------------------------
# Google Analytics 4 measurement ID. Leave blank to disable analytics.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_GA_ID=G-XXXXXXXXXX

# --- OpenSky Network (optional) ---------------------------------------------
# OAuth2 client credentials for the server-side trace fallback
# (src/lib/trails/source/server-trace-service.ts). Without these, Aeris
# still works — the trace service falls back to public adsb.lol / readsb
# endpoints. Provide both values or neither.
#
# Create a client at https://opensky-network.org/my-opensky (Account → API).
# OPENSKY_CLIENT_ID=
# OPENSKY_CLIENT_SECRET=

# --- OpenAIP (optional) -----------------------------------------------------
# API key for the airspace vector-tile proxy
# (src/app/api/airspace-tiles/route.ts). Without this, the airspace
# overlay toggle will produce empty responses; flight rendering is
# unaffected. Get a key from https://www.openaip.net (Account → API keys).
#
# Remember: OpenAIP data is CC BY-NC 4.0 — attribution is already rendered
# in-app but non-commercial use is on you.
# OPENAIP_API_KEY=

# --- Simulation (optional) --------------------------------------------------
# URL of the local simulation server (sim_server.py). Defaults to
# http://localhost:8888 when the ?provider=simulation URL param is set.
# SIMULATION_SERVER_URL=http://localhost:8888

# --- Notes ------------------------------------------------------------------
# Public ADS-B providers (airplanes.live, adsb.lol) are called directly
# from the browser with CORS, so they do not need credentials.
